29:09.752 --> 29:10.793
in military. In other words, it was the first real 
big step in overcoming my

29:12.294 --> 29:25.147
poor environment as a poor kid. I began to rise 
above it, and I loved it. And it was shortly after my

29:31.366 --> 29:45.424
graduation from high school in ROTC and being a 
member of the National Guard, which continued on

29:31.366 --> 29:45.424
for two or three years until I entered the flying 
contest in 1938, that I knew I was going to stay with

29:31.366 --> 29:45.424
the military. So you had already made up your mind 
as a young man that you wanted to have a military

29:46.905 --> 29:52.573
career? I had made up my mind in my latter teenage 
years that I was going to have a military career.

29:59.125 --> 30:01.748
